inn1.comm: full delivery on the middle first up, driven down to mid-on
short of length angling in from wide off the crease, Finch leaves it alone
another one from wide off the crease, slightly fuller and Finch comes forward to drive it to cover
fuller delivery on the middle stump, pushed towards mid-on and the two take off immediately. The throw hits Finch and ricochets almost all the way to the ropes
comes forward to the full delivery and defends towards mid-off
143 ks, fuller length on off stump, Khawaja comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
short and very wide, loose start from Holder
another short delivery, but this is outside off stump and Finch goes for the pull, good stop at square leg
length ball on the pads, he tries to flick it but misses, gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls down to fine leg
length ball on off and middle, Uzzie stays in the crease and defends it towards the leg side
edged, and just drops short of the fielder at second slip. It was bowled on a length outside off and Uzzie didn't really go forward to that. Lucky there
wristy flick through the leg side, but fine leg cuts it off. It went very close to the left of him. Would have been a certain boundary had it been hit a meter away from the fielder
now he dishes a short and wide delivery and Finch stays on the back foot, cuts it through point with just timing
fuller ball wide outside off, left alone by the batsman
he goes for the drive off a fuller delivery outside off, slices it towards point. The fielder doesn't stop it cleanly and it allows a single
full and on the pads, Finch gets good placement with his flick, it runs down to the deep backward square leg boundary with ease
pulls the length back a bit, it is still on a length, defended off the front foot
back of length outside off, Finch cuts even though there is not much room, places it past point and third-man has to come around and field
fuller delivery on off and middle, angling in, driven to wide mid-on
a short of length ball on off, angling across the left-hander, Uzzie goes for the pull, but the extra bounce takes it past the outside edge
fuller length delivery, the batsman comes forward and defends towards leg side
fuller length on off stump, Uzzie comes forward and defends it towards the off side
length ball on off stump, pushed towards short midwicket off the front foot
short of length, but it's on the pads, Uzzie Khawaja hops and tucks it down to fine leg
length ball angling in, Finch comes forward and pushes it to square leg
length ball on off stump, the batsman drives it on the up but straight to extra cover

caught at square leg! Oh wow!  That is a double-handed ripper. It was a length ball on the middle stump and Khawaja went for a flick, he timed it really well and I thought it was heading towards the boundary, but Powell at square-leg dives full length to his right, catches the ball while in air and cuts off Uzzie's innings.
he is greeted with a quick bouncer which sails over his head
short of length delivery, angling across the batsman, left alone
145 ks, fuller length delivery outside off nearly takes the edge, Hughes was playing the drive but that went very close to the edge
this time he gets and edge, but it trickles down to third-man boundary. Hughes was squared up in his defence by that short of length delivery on off stump
length ball, but very wide, Finch think about going after it, but leaves it alone
length ball on the pads, Finch turns it towards midwicket but it goes straight to the fielder
fuller length just outside off, Finch comes forward but leaves it at the last moment
short of length wide of off, wobbles a bit in the air too, left alone again
short of length outside off, but instead of going for a cut he goes for the straight pull, finds the fielder at mid-on
full and wide outswinger, it swings past the wide marker
whoah! that was cut with some ferocity and Finch lets out a grunt as he hits it straight to the fielder at cover point
short of length delivery on off stump, Hughes shuffles across and has to get up on his toes to defend that one
fuller delivery outside off, going away with the angle, Hughes comes forward and leaves it alone
too full, and it comes quickly towards the batsman, Hughes jams his bat down and finds the gap at cover. It doesn't go all the way and they run back for three
short of length delivery on off stump, the batsman hops and defends it back down the pitch
147 ks, length ball on the pads, too quick for the batsman as he goes for the flick, but gets hit on the pads
146, short of length delivery on off, Hughes is pushed right back and he has to jump on his toes to defend that
short of length outside off, Finch cuts it straight to point

caught at cover! One handed! Another catch plucked from nowhere. Finch went back to the short of length delivery outside off and smashed it, reallly smashed it. The only thing was that he hit in the air, and Bravo pulls off a super reflex catch. he went with two hands, but only could get a hand on it as it went too quick to him
short of length outside off, left alone
slightly fuller and in the channel outside off, left alone
angles in from wide off the crease, it is short of length on off stump but Clarke leaves it on the bounce
fuller length a touch wide of off, Clarke comes forward and shoulders arms
quick short ball, Hughes has enough time to duck under
length ball on off stump, Hughes comes forward and defends it down the pitch
short of length outside off, Hughes goes back to cut, but gets an outside edge past gully. Holder at third-man makes a full-length diving stop
145 ks, short of length on off stump, Clarke gets up on his toes and defends to the off side
comes forward to place the ball in the gap at cover as soon as he sees the fuller length
short of length outside off, bounces a touch extra and Clarke sways away from it
bowls it full and wide of off, called a wide
keeps it on a length wide of off, no problems for Hughes in letting that one go
short of length delivery beats the outside edge. Hughes stays in the crease as he tries to defend that and doesn't cover the line of the ball
this time he leaves it alone as it is still wide of off stump
back of length on off stump, he goes back and punches it through cover point for a couple
oh wooow! Super timing and it made a good sound as well. It was just short of length and he quickly went for the pull, it goes flat and over the square leg boundary
leaves the length ball wide outside off without much problem
120 ks, gentle length delivery on off stump to start off, pushed to cover off the back foot
bit of width outside off and Clarke places it beautifully through cover point, no power only timing in that one, it just races to the boundary
fuller length outside off, Clarke comes comfortably forward and drives it on the up to mid-off
keeps it on a length wide of off, the batsman has to stretch out to defend that
and he keeps it there, wide of off, Clarke comes forward and lets it go
oh nice! He comes forward, and with Sammy's pace, he has enough time to place that drive to the right of the widish mid-off fielder, beautifully driven
he floats it wide and full outside off, it would have been a wide, but Hughes throws his bat at it and it goes in the air through cover point down to the fielder in the deep
126ks, length ball outside off, angling in from wide off the crease, left alone
he bowls a yorker on off stump, punched towards mid-on
length ball on off stump, Clarke comes forward and lets it go
length ball wide of off, Clarke comes forward and drives it away from the body, straight to point
gets a full delivery outside off and he drives it handsomely through extra cover, that races along on the turf, the fielder at deep cover had no chance
more driving through the off side, this time it is Hughes who plays a mirror image shot of what Clarke played previous ball, beats the man at deep cover easily
back of length on off stump, defended toward the off side off the back foot
length ball on off stump, he comes forward and defends it towards cover

caught at midwicket! Oh no! There goes another one to a shot he would have thought was going towards the boundary. It was a hit-me delivery, short of length on the body, and Hughes goes for a pull. He had all the time at Sammy's pace, but he neither places it on the ground, or high up in the air, hits it straight to Darren Bravo at midwicket.
length ball wide outside off, Clarke comes forward and lets it go
length ball a touch outside off, left alone easily

Timber!!!! full delivery on the middle stump, a bit quicker from Bravo and Clarke looks to flick it through the leg side, but misses the ball completely and hears the clatter of the stumps behind him. That is a huge huge wicket.
gets off the mark with a super straight drive. Bravo bowled it full in search of swing which wasn't there, Wade comes forward and drives it all the way down the ground
full and wide outside off, left alone easily
length ball on off stump, Wade comes forward and defends it to the off side
way down the leg side, exercise for the Umpire
length ball on off stump, Wade comes forward and opens the face to run the ball towards point
length ball wide of off stump, the batsman watches it go through to the keeper
quicker on the middle stump line, tucked away towards short fine
flighted on middle and off, the batsman comes forward and defends
flatter delivery, spins a touch, defended off the back foot
goes back and punches this one to the cover for a single
flat and quick, turns in, turned towards short-leg fielder
he goes back to turn it to the leg side, but gets and inside edge on to the pads
full delivery outside off, Wade comes forward to drive but can't beat the fielder at mid-off
full delivery on off stump, driven back to the left of the bowler, who makes a good stop
oh my god! That was almost wicket no. 5. It was a full length delivery on off stump and Bailey went for a full-blooded drive, he gets an inside edge that just runs past the leg stump, very lucky
stays on the back foot and cuts the length delivery outside off to third man
fuller length on off stump, Wade aims towards the leg side this time, drives it straight to mid-on
length ball on off stump, angling in to the batsman, turned to midwicket off the front foot
turns in to the batsman, and hits the batsman high on the pads
pushes it through outside off, defended off the back foot
he shuffles across outside off and works it on the on side towards short fine
he comes forward and defends the flighted delivery to the off side
gets a short one outside off that is turning away, he cuts it to deep point
flatter and quicker on off stump, tucked away towards midwicket off the back foot
fuller length on off and middle, driven past midwicket but only goes as far as wide mid on
length delivery outside off, he pushes at it and the bat rotates in his hand, the ball goes towards cover
length ball on off stump, he comes forward and drives it back to the bowler
length ball on off, Bailey doesn't really come forward and the ball takes an inside edge and hits his pads
slightly slower wide outside off, the batsman has to stretch and plays it away from his body towards point
full and almost around the wide-marker, Bailey bends his knees and drives it to deep cover
flight and turn into the batsman, it takes the inside edge, not to far from that close -in fielder on the leg side
this one was quicker and he steers it past point for three
flighted delivery on off stump, turns away from the batsman, who pulls his bat out at the last moment
the length is slightly shorter this time, allows the batsman to go back and punch it to deep cover
another inside edge on to the pads, this time falling on the off side
flatter delivery on off stump, turns in a bit, pushed to midwicket off the back foot
fuller length on off stump, no swing on offer and Wade comfortably drives it down the ground to long-off
length ball outside off stump, the batsman comes forward and steers it to third-man for a single
draws an edge with a delivery angling across the batsman, Wade was squared up as he tried to defend and the edge goes past first slip, down to third-man
out of nowhere he pulls out an aerial shot. It was a full delivery on the middle stump line, and the batsman tried to go towards midwicket, gets a leading edge actually over the bowler's head
some swing for Bravo but it starts too wide of off
play and a miss wide outside off! Bailey didn't need to play at that one as it was very wide outside off, the ball goes very close to the outside edge. Bravo hold his head..
closer to the stumps and it's fuller in length, the batsman comes forward and drives it to cover
tossed up delivery outside off, squeezed out towards point, Wade sends Bailey back
flighted delivery on off, doesn't turn as much and Wade gets an inside edge to the leg side
turns it to short fine leg off the front foot
flighted delivery on the off stump, Bailey comes forward and pushes it to midwicket
similar delivery as the last one, this time he knocks it in the gap and picks up a single at long-on
tossed up on leg and middle stump line, Wade comes forward and pushes it to mid-on off the front foot
short of length on off stump, the batsman stays in the crease and drives it towards deep cover off the back foot
length ball on off stump, the batsman comes forward and pushes it on the up to cover
cracked hard off the back foot, but again, the batsman finds the fielder, this time it's Pollard at point
that flies through gully! He wanted to drive it through cover, but the ball takes an outside edge and goes safely towards third-man
length ball wide outside off, Bailey goes forward and runs it down to deep backward point with an open face
floated up to the batsman on off stump, Wade drives it down the ground to long-off for a single
angles in and turns away from Wade, who cuts it to deep point off the back foot
floated up to the batsman, but it is on the leg stump line, Bailey tries to flick but misses, it hits the pads and runs down to fine-leg boundary
tossed up on the pads again, worked around to short fine leg
flighted all the way to the batsman, on off stump, the batsman drives it with the turn to deep midwicket
whoa!!! That was short and it came in to the batsman at some pace. Wade was looking to cut and he chops it very close to the stumps, lucky

caught at first slip! Oh what a blinder from the captain! Wade goes for the cut again, this time the ball didn't come back into him, but bounced extra. He gets a healthy edge towards first slip, but it travels fast and high, and Sammy shows excellent reflexes by pulling off a super one-hander over his head
short of length delivery outside off, Bailey goes back in a flash and cracks a pull through midwicket, all along the ground
118 kph, slower on off stump, pushed to cover off the front foot
a good delivery on off stump, the batsman gets squared up and edges it down to third-man

Chopped on! Oh the Aussies are crumbling here.. Shot, no shot, whatever. Maxwell, who score a fifty last innings, tries to pull his bat out of the way of a length delivery outside off, he is too late though. The ball hits the inside edge and drops on to his stumps. More joy for captain Sammy
length ball on off stump, slow ball and Faulkner has to wait for it. He defends it to the off side
short of length outside off, Faulkner goes back and pushes it to cover
flighted and full on off stump, the batsman comes forward and drives it down to long-on
back of length quicker delivery outside off, played towards the gully off the back foot
tossed up outside off, turns into the batsman, he plays it off the back foot
tossed up further to the batsman, he comes forward and pushes it to mid-off
flatter quicker delivery that goes across the batsman, beats the outside edge as the batsman has a poke at it
length ball on off stump, defended off the front foot
length on off stump again, the batsman comes forward and opens the face to play it towards gully
off the back foot this time, it's steered to point off a slightly short of length delivery
wide delivery and the batsman has a wild swing at it, it goes past the outside edge
ohh! Another outside edge, the batsman plays at a swinging delivery without any feet movement, it wasn't very far from Gayle at gully
fuller length wide of off, the batsman watches the line carefully and lets it go
length delivery outside off stump, pushed to point off the back foot
flighted delivery on off stump, defended to the leg side off the front foot
full and flighted on the stumps, pushed to midwicket
turns in from around off stump, tucked away on the leg side
poor delivery as this goes down the leg side, paddled down to the fine-leg boundary easily
flatter delivery outside off, turns in and it's worked away to deep backward square leg
and almost another wicket. Super piece of work by Pollard at short leg, as he flicks the ball back to the stumps in one quick motion. Faulker just got back in time
short of length delivery outside off, he gets an under edge to Gayle at gully
and almost a run-out this time! Bailey takes off immediately after dropping the ball on the off side, Pollard from point cuts it off and aims at non-striker's. Would have been a gonner had he hit
back of length delivery, defended towards point off the back foot
keeps it back of length outside off, defended to point off the back foot again
short of length delivery on off stump, defended off the back foot to cover
he gets some width outside off and he stands tall and punches that one through cover for his first boundary. No one in the deep
short of length outside off, punched hard to cover where the ball bursts through Gayle's hands. The batsmen take couple
back of length delivery outside off, left alone easily
length ball outside off stump, the batsman comes forward and steers it to point
short of length delivery on the body, it is tucked away to fine leg by the batsman
short of length delivery on off stump, the batsman has to hop on his toes to defend that one to the off side
comes in with the angle on to his body, the batsman pushes it past midwicket for a single off the back foot
length ball on off stump, guided down to third-man off the outside half of his bat
fuller outside off, swings away a touch, the batsman wanted to drive it to the off side, but it hits the inside half and goes towards mid-on
another full delivery outside off, pushed to the gap at cover for a single
length ball outside off stump, the batsman comes forward and defends it towards cover
some width for the batsman and he takes advantage by cutting it hard to deep cover off the back foot
waits on the back foot and tries to steer the length delivery to third-man, but can't beat Gayle at gully
fuller length delivery on off stump, punched back to the bowler
back of length angled delivery on off stump, defended off the back foot down the pitch
he shuffles across and works the short of length delivery to deep square leg off the back foot
fuller length outside off, Bailey bends his knees and plays a forcing drive to deep cover
a quick short delivery on off stump, Faulkner fends at it, taking his eyes away from the ball, and drops it towards the leg side. The batsmen take a quick single
squeezed out to deep backward point for a quick couple of runs
gets good bounce with a short of length delivery outside off, chopped towards point off the back foot
oh that jags back into the batsman, hits the batsman around thigh-pad and flies to the keeper.
fuller length delivery on off stump, the batsman comes forward and drives to mid-off
plays that one softly off the back foot towards mid-on and calls for a quick single
leading edge goes through first slip. But Gayle has been moved to gully from there and it goes through to the boundary. The batsman was looking to turn that on the leg side and was squared-up
back of length of off stump, defended off the back foot down the pitch
fires it on the leg stump and that is easily glanced down to fine leg
he calls for a quick single with a push towards mid-on and gets there comfortably
another quick single, this time to mid-off, off a full delivery
full delivery on the stumps, this time he pushes it a bit hard towards mid-on and thus there is no chance of a single
back of length delivery on off stump, slightly slower, tucked away to midwicket off the back foot

there comes the slower ball! It hits the batsman on the pads as he fell forward. Big appeal but the umpire says no. Sammy thinks otherwise and calls for a review. The replays show the ball just missing the leg stump. It looked very close in the first instance
gets steep bounce around off stump from just back of a length, defended back down the pitch
inside edge bounces over the stumps as the batsman tried to defend the short of length delivery, not very far again
the bowler attempts a quick bouncer, but it easily bounces over the batsman
and another one, he gets a lot of bounce with those ones slammed hard on the deck. Goes way over
back of length, but it's on the pads and is easily turned away to deep backward square for a couple
it was back of length around off stump, but with Holder's height, it was always going over the stumps, left alone
into the batsman's body, it is easily worked away behind square on the leg side for another single
keeps it a touch outside off, the batsman gets up on his toes and defends it to the off side
short delivery and the batsman goes for a pull, doesn't get hold of it as his hand comes off the handle, it goes down to deep backward square
length ball on off stump, slight away swing, driven down to long-on
short of length delivery, cutting in to the batsman, he tries to flick it down to fine leg but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad
a yorker outside off stump, the batsman gets an under-edge to the wicketkeeper
length ball on off, it is pushed off the front foot to mid-off who is standing a little deep
slower delivery on the middle stump line, the batsman waits for it and flicks it to deep midwicket for a single
arches back and cuts the shorter length delivery on off stump over the point fielder for a welcome boundary
makes room by moving outside leg and cuts this one all along the ground through cover point, it goes through a diving Darren Bravo and Bailey brings up his half-century
another forceful shot, this time it's a pull off a short delivery to deep backward square leg
slightly slower on off stump, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler off the front foot
more runs, this is more of what Maxwell was doing in the last game. Faulkner charges out and moves outside leg, flat bats the short of length delivery all along the ground to midwicket boundary
this time he stays in the crease, but goes for the pull anyway. The fielder at deep midwicket cuts it off
slower ball on off stump, the batsman wanted to play it on off, but ends up pushing it towards midwicket
back of length delivery on off stump, the batsman tries to work it to the leg side but gets a leading edge towards cover
makes room by moving outside leg and goes through with a big swing, but it was a slower ball and he misses it completely
back of length on off stump, he opens the face and runs it to the left of Pollard at point
fuller length on the pads, driven down to deep midwicket
attempts a yorker but it turns out to be a full-toss on the pads, the batsman misses out as he gets an inside edge on to his pads
starts off with a flat delivery on the stumps, it is pushed to long-on off the back foot
full and flighted on off stump, the batsman comes forward and pushes that to cover
that's the straighter one (or the one going other way), goes past the outside edge
a quicker delivery on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
he still can't get it away, it is full and flighted and it's pushed to cover
now the conventional offspinner, turns in and hits the pads as the batsman comes forward to defend
short and wide and that is cut hard, but there is a wall called Pollard that his hard to breach
he goes to the other side with a flick down to deep backward square where Powell makes a sliding save
gives himself some room and dabs the length delivery on the middle stump towards third-man
it's is outside off and it's again dabbed to the left of Pollard at point
back of length on the stumps, the batsman gets beside the line and plays a late cut to third-man
it is a slower ball outside off stump and the batsman completely misses it as he aims for the leg side
quicker delivery on off stump, pushed to the off side off the back foot
flighted on the off stump line, turns towards leg, it is tucked down to fine-leg for a single
fuller delivery outside off and that is pushed softly to cover, the batsmen complete a tight single
flatter delivery short of length on off stump, he goes back and punches it straight to cover
some extras here as this one turns down the leg side, oh, the umpire gives it as some runs. Probably there was a faint tickle, hard to tell
tossed up outside off stump, the batsman dabs it towards the vacant square leg area and calls for two, but the keeper runs around and keeps them to one
he bowls length on off stump, the batsman punches it down the ground to long-on
length ball on off stump, a touch slower, pushed back to the bowler
he comes forward and drives the length delivery outside off to cover, who is standing a bit deep
makes room by moving outside leg, it is carved to deep cover
he comes from wide off the crease and bowls a shorter length delivery, the batsman goes for the pull but makes no connection
waits on the backfoot for this one on the off stump line, opens the face but it goes straight to Pollard at backward point
big offspinner, turns into Bailey, who does well to punch it towards cover off the back foot
he comes forward and pushes the flighted ball to the right of point fielder
slightly short outside off stump, the batsman stays in the crease and pulls it to deep midwicket
this goes the other way, and the batsman does well to cut it hard and beat the man at backward point
tossed up on off stump, he comes forward and defends to off side
another one that goes away, but the length is too short and allows the batsman to adjust and play that to the left of backward point
fuller length delivery outside off, driven off the front foot to deep cover for a single
walks across the stumps and tries to push a delivery from wide of off to the leg side but gets a leading edge to third-man boundary
length ball on off stump, dabbed towards backward point
this time he beats the backward point fielder and third-man takes a long time to come around, they run a couple
short and wide outside off, cut to deep point off the back foot
full and wide outside off, it takes another outside edge but Sarwan at third-man comes around a bit quicker this time and keeps the batsmen to a single
back of length angling in to the batsman, who opens the face and dabs it towards point for a quick single
he goes for the pull and it hit straight to Gayle at midwicket, the batsmen set off for a single anyway. Gayle had to hit the stumps, but he missed
moves way outside off stump, but gets full yorker that hits the pads and goes towards short fine, Bailey was on the floor as he fell offbalance
shorter length ball is pushed towards midwicket but the two take a single
back of length on off, the batsman punches it to deep cover for a single
ahh, well done by the keeper as he stops an inside edge that looked headed towards the boundary
length ball, it is driven off the front foot to extra cover for a single which brings the century of this stand.

caught at deep midwicket! So there is the wicket, they had to wait almost 20 overs for it. Faulkner makes room by moving outside leg and tries to flat-bat that to the stands at deep midwicket but it goes high, and is caught just inside the boundary by Powell, who didn't have to move much at all
length delivery on off stump, pushed towards mid-on with soft hands for a quick single
called a wide as this one sails over the batsman, it was wide outside off too
angles across the left-hander who thrusts his front foot out and lets it go through
short of length delivery angling across the batsman, Johnson pulls it in front of square to wide long-on
he responds with a length delivery outside off that goes past the outside edge
and they are on their way, it is full and on off stump, the batsman drives it hard past the bowler to the straight boundary
and more runs, this time it is short of length and quickly swivel and pulls it down to the gap at deep backward square
full and wide outside off, driven straight to cover, but they take a single
goes across the batsman who gets his bat out of the way of the ball
full on the pads, he flicks it to deep backward square leg
length ball with a lot of width outside off, cracked down to third-man for a single, Bailey keeps the strike
fuller delivery on off stump, it is swatted down to deep midwicket, but there was a fielder there and he keeps the batsmen to a single
back of length on off stump, he gets square up a bit as he pushes this towards point
it is a slower ball wide outside off, but the batsman adjusts and pulls it down to deep midwicket
low full toss outside off, Johnson fails to take advantage as he hits it straight to mid-off
waits on the back foot and pushes it to deep point, where a fumble by Powell allows a couple
quick yorker on the pads, it is dug out towards midwicket
short of length delivery on middle stump, pulled in front of square for a single
a very wide slower ball, would have been called, but Bailey throws his bat at it and hits it towards deep extra cover for a couple
another slower ball wide outside off, the batsman waits for it and hits it to deep extra cover with a flat-batted shot
full and wide outside off, it's in the arc and Johnson drives it straight down the ground, it bounces once before hitting the advertising boards
it wasn't too short, but Johnson goes for the pull and hits it straight to Gayle at backward square leg
it is a low full-toss and Johnson finds Gayle again with his flick, just a single. He could have hit it anywhere really

overthrows bring Bailey back into strike, it was dabbed towards deep point, and the batsmen call for a couple, the throw comes to the keeper, who then fires it towards non-striker where no one backs it up
makes room and drives the full delivery straight to extra cover fielder
low full toss on the pads, punched down to long-on
another low full-toss and he drives it hard down to long-on
slower delivery on off stump, it is short of length too, Johnson waits and tucks it to the leg side for a single
That's it!! It's a wonderful hundred and he brings it up with a wonderful swat over long-on off a low full-toss. Brilliant innings given the context of the game
short of length on off stump, pulled in front of square, to deep midwicket
slower ball outside off, the batsman has to wait a long time for the ball, he then just flat bats it over the bowler's head. Pollard tries hard, but is not able to stop the ball.
same ball, but this time he gets more on it, it goes over the rope and hits the ad-boards
dropped by Pollard. Very harsh, but given the fielding standards today, that is what it is I am afraid. It was a lofted shot and Pollard dived full-length but can't quite pull it off
length ball of off and Bravo is leaking has let the floodgates open here, this one goes over long on into the stands. Pollard can just watch..
What-a-way-to-finish! This time he goes over extra cover and gets a whole lot of bat on it, it sails deep into the crowd at extra cover.. what an innings and what a way to finish!

inn2.comm: short of length delivery going across Gayle, left alone easily
length ball outside off, just a push to wide mid-off gets Gayle his first runs
full and swinging, but it's down the leg side and it flicks the pads on its way to the fine-leg boundary
now beats him outside off with one which carries on with the angle, Powell stayed rooted in the crease
pushes it further up to the batsman who comes half-forward to drive and edges it through gully for a single
back of length on off stump, Gayle stands tall and pushes it to the right of mid-off for a single
bowls it full, but it's down the leg side and is called a wide. It wasn't far from leg stump though as Gayle had moved across
142ks, that kicks from a short of length and leaves the batsman too, Gayle was surprised and moved out of the way  just in time
full and on the pads, 142 ks, Gayle jams his bat down and pushes it towards midwicket
fuller length on the off and middle, turned away to deep backward square leg

that's it! It's all over, Gayle talks to Powell and thinks about a review, Powell says no chance. It was full and swinging away, it pitched around off and Gayle was hit right in front as he got squared-up a bit. Starc strikes in his first over..
length ball on off, doesn't swing much into the batsman, Sarwan takes a positive stride and pushes it to the off side

it is a gonner! He thought that the over had finished, but it hadn't. The ball is a perfect left-armer's delivery, pitches on length on the middle stump line, and curves back in. Sarwan had taken a step forward but wasn't able to take his foot out of the way, stuck in front and he was dead the moment he missed it..
length ball wide outside off, easily left alone and it's rightly callled a wide
back of length of off stump, Powell stays on the back foot and steers it down to third man
it's on a length outside off and it carries on with the angle, left alone easily
back of length on the middle and leg line, Lara tucks it to square leg off the back foot
back of length on off stump, defended down the pitch off the back foot
fuller length on off stump, he comes forward and pushes it to cover
back of length outside off, angled away from the left-hander, left alone
full and swinging away from the left hander, it was slightly outside off too, left alone
back of length outside off, 145 ks, doesn't swing much this one, left alone by the batsman
angles into the batsman from wide off the crease, not much swing and the batsman defends it off the back foot
keeps it tight in the channel, 146 ks, slight wobble away from the batsman, the batsman lets it go
slightly fuller outside off, swings away from the batsman, who stays patient and shoulders arms
he goes down the leg side, but the batsman is unable to get it away, it hits the pads on its way to the keeper
this one is too far down the leg side
this time it is wide on the other side, McKay pushes it wide of off
now he brings it back around off stump, the angle takes the ball away from the left-hander and beats the outside edge
back of length on off stump, pushed towards point off the back foot
fuller length ball on off, Powell comes right forward and defends it solidly to the off side
Oiii! Full and angled across the batsman and Powell decides to go for an expansive drive, misses as the ball goes past the outside edge
short of length on the middle stump, tucked away to deep backward square leg off the back foot
crack! he stays on the back foot and gives the short of length delivery on off a good thwack, it races past point
back of length a touch outside off, Powell goes back and wanted to defend towards off, but the ball takes an inside edge to the leg side
loses direction as he pushes it down the leg side
fuller length outside off, Powell stays in the crease and defends it back to the bowler
pushes it up to the batsman and gives him width too, Powell goes for a driven without moving his feet and inside-edges it towards the leg side
143ks, short of length delivery on off and middle, Bravo hops and defends it to the leg side
beautifully times it off his legs, but straight to square leg fielder.
short of length outside off, Bravo watches it carefully and sways out of line
back of length on off stump line, the batsman stays on the back foot and defends
fuller length on off stump, the batsman drives it powerfully, but straight to mid-off
he pulls the length back a little, Powell gets up on his toes and tucks it towards midwicket
he does it again, Powell goes for a drive without getting anywhere close to the ball, gets beaten
length ball outside off, he takes a step forward and pushes it towards the off side
woaa.. A nothing shot from Powell, he stays in the crease and tries to pull a length delivery over mid-on, the leading edge takes it just over mid-off
he goes down the leg side again, it's called a wide
short and wide, beautifully cracked over point, brings back some nostalgia ..
full on the pads, he flicks it beautifully, but it goes straight to square leg
oh how gorgeous is that!! Length ball, not much swing outside off, he takes a step forward drives it though square all along the ground..
back of length on off stump, pushed toward point off the front foot
quick short delivery on the body, he ducks under it in time..

and the nostalgic picture is torn apart by a full delivery from Starc! He had been bowling a slightly shorter length this over, and now he pushes it full and on the stumps and Lara is late to bring his bat down, that was hitting middle of middle. Bravo reviews in hope, but that was out even to a blind eye...
back of length on off stump, the batsman waits and opens the face of the bat at the last moment
length ball bowled across the right-hander, he stays in the crease and shoulders arms
length ball on off stump, Dwayne gets squared up a bit as he defends this to the off side
plays away from his body at this short and wide delivery outside off, pushes it to point
goes past the outside edge and Dwayne doesn't cover the line of the ball in his forward defence
another one that goes across the right-hander, this time Dwayne goes forward and gets his bat out of the way
142 ks, short of length delivery outside off, left alone by the batsman
length ball on off stump line, 144 ks, Powell comes forward and defends it towards point
brute of a shot! and Uzzie makes a diving save to cut it off. Powell crunched it to covers with some power, but Khawaja stops a certain boundary
comedy, he misfields this time and gives away a single. It was just a push in Uzzie's direction, no high-fives this time.
146 k quick bouncer on the body, Bravo ducks under it awkwardly
147 ks, back of length delivery on off stump, Bravo hops on his toes to defend that to the leg side
hits the thigh pad after pitching around middle stump line on a short of length as Powell looked to turn it to leg side
keeps it very tight around off stump, defended off the back foot towards off
short and wide outside off, Powell goes for a cut shot and misses, the ball goes past the outside edges
wow! He flicks it in front of square as nonchalantly as you like. It was a full length delivery and he just chipped it, it goes all the way
length ball on off stump, he comes forward and drives it hard but straight to cover
drives it in the air towards cover, and it was just to the left of the fielder at short-ish cover, goes to extra cover on the bounce
back of length on off stump, defended towards the leg side
angles across the right hander, but it's a touch wide outside off, Dwayne keeps his bat behind his head
another one across the right-hander, but Bravo goes for a square drive, playing at this one away from the body, straight to point though
he gets one on the pads, and it swings a touch into the batsman too, hits the pads and rolls down to the fine-leg boundary
length ball on off stump, Bravo gets solidly behind it and defends
back of length on the middle stump line, Bravo hops and tucks it off his hips down to fine leg
back of length in the channel outside off, goes straight on, Bravo keeps his bat out of the line of the ball
crunched over cover stylishly off a length ball, it goes one bounce to the boundary and looks pretty too.
pulls the length backa bit, it is defended off the back foot
quick back of a length delivery outside off, left alone easily
stays patient, leaves one more outside off
lures him with a fuller one outside off, Bravo doesn't take the bait, leaves alone
145 ks, back of length outside off, Powell has looked solid today and he defends this comfortably off the back foot to the off side
i spoke too soon, this one goes past the outside edge as Powell doesn't move his feet at all to this length delivery outside off, he hangs his bat tamely at that one
this one is closer to the line of off stump, Powell goes back and across and defends it solidly back to the bowler
goes for an aerial shot but doesn't really get much timing behind that one. It was a fuller delivery on off and he ends up chipping it over wide mid-on for a couple
148 ks, length ball on off stump, Powell stays behind the line and defends it back to the bowler
quick bouncer outside off this time, Powell easily ducks under it
length ball on off stump, Bravo shoulders arms
full delivery outside off, Bravo drives it hard straight down the ground, but it goes to mid-off
oh sweet! just for a couple though. Slightly short of length and Bravo goes for a pull, he gets it high, but not much distance on that as it drops over the midwicket fielder
super timing by Bravo, the ball was full and he just lifts it and sends it into the stands over long-off
and more runs, he tries to go off side, but ends up going past mid-on as the bat turns in his hands..
the bowler now pulls the length back, it is dabbed towards third-man off the back foot
and he keeps going over the infield. Slightly full on off and he Bravo gets under is and slams it to the extra-cover boundary
short of length going across Bravo, left alone
he sees it in his half and he goes after it, this time it's over mid-on ..
slightly slower delivery, 132 ks, on a length on off stump, Bravo gets behind it and defends
146 k bouncer on the body, Bravo gets under it. There is a deep square leg in place for a pull.
147 k snorter! It was on short of length and takes off like a rocket from the pitch. Bravo does well to arch back to get out the way
flights on the middle and he is driven down the ground to long-off, Maxwell collides with Bravo as he dives..
flighted delivery on off, he comes forward and pushes it to cover
comes down the pitch but ends up flicking towards short fine as the ball spun
sees the flight and he gets down on his knee and hammers it to deep midwicket boundary
and another one by Powell, the difference is that this time he hits it in the air...
tossed up delivery on off stump, Powell leans forward and defends
back of length delivery on the middle stump line, Bravo gets up on his toes and defends it solidly back to the bowler
141ks bouncer on the body, but it sails way over the batsman and is called a wide
was that off the bat! short of a length delivery, Bravo gets something on it to the leg side, Wade dives and makes a good stop and fires a throw at the non-striker's.. could have been very close
he takes his front leg out to play the full length delivery, gets and inside edge and Wade dives to his right to stop the runs
full delivery on the middle stump, driven firmly to mid-on
quick shorter delivery outside the line of off stump, Powell moves out of the way and looks at the leg umpire, who says it's fine..
146 ks, comes into the left hander slightly from a length, punched back towards the bowler
Oh my!! How good is that one! It was a flatter delivery on off stump and he just lifted it up over extra cover, it goes all the way over and deep into the stands.
he pushes the tossed up delivery towards point and takes off for a quick single
flighted on off, Powell drops it towards off side and steals another quick single
flighted on off and middle, Bravo comes forward and drives it down to long-on for a single
bowls filth down the leg side and it is swept hard to the fine-leg boundary
spin and bounce outside off, he tossed this one a bit wide of off, Powell came forward but gets beaten
he bowls it full on the pads, Bravo is not able to flick it properly as he fall over to the off side, gets a single to backward square leg though
length ball on the middle stump line, 145 ks, pushed to midwicket off the back foot
length ball on the pads, Powell swats it to deep square leg and brings up the team's hundred
it is short of length, but it is down the leg side too, Bravo hops and flicks it off his hips towards fine leg
147k, full and swinging delivery on off stump, punched firmly to the right of mid-on for a single
length ball on off stump, solidly defended off the back foot by Bravo
length delivery on off stump, Powell dabs it towards point but straight to the fielder
length and wide of off, Powell drives it away from the body, but with some confidence and flourish, the ball is stopped by a diving Finch at extra cover boundary
gets beaten outside off to this one which is closer to off, plays way inside the line of the ball
and gets beaten again, this time on the front foot, as the ball swings past the blade
stays on the back foot and dabs it to the right of the point fielder for a single
back of length delivery, angling across Bravo. He waits and opens the face to run it down to third-man
short of length delivery on off stump, defended solidly off the back foot
back of length on the middle stump line, Bravo hops and punches it to deep midwicket for a single
a quick short ball aimed very well on the body, right around the throat. There is no way getting away from those ones. Powell does well to drop it down to the off side

booooom! length ball on off stump, now Powell takes his front leg out and gives a massive swing, and sends it over the long-on boundary for a six out of nowhere.. I thought Bravo was the one playing those shots
short delivery on the body, Powell has to jump up as he defends that down the pitch
another short ball, but it gets high up around the chest area, fended towards backward square leg for a single
short of length delivery goes down the leg side, Paul Reiffel, the umpire, stretches his wings..
114 ks, it's a slow leg-cutter outside off and goes past the outside edge
drives away from the body at this wid-ish length delivery outside, slices it down to third man
bowls the slower ball again, but it's full up to the batsman and Bravo turns it towards square leg off the front foot for a single
another leg-spinner type delivery, defended from the crease towards the off side
the normal one now, 138ks, Powell stays on the back foot and cuts the short of length ball down to third-man
and another slower ball, this time on the leg-stump. Bravo is unable to get it away and gets hit on the pads
another short ball on the body, Powell goes for a hook but doesn't get much bat on it. Lucky for him as it drops short of fine-leg fielder
back of length delivery outside off stump, comes a bit slow off the surface, Bravo opens the face and runs it down to third-man
length delivery on off stump, driven beautifully with a high elbow back down the pitch, Johnson does well to get down quickly and stop that one
short of length delivery across the left-hander from round the stumps, defended towards off easily off the back foot
slightly slower at 128 ks, short of length delivery outside off, dabbed down to third-man for a single
short delivery, but it wasn't as quick as Bravo expected. He went for the pull, but the ball arrives later and goes through him to the keeper
back of length delivery on off stump, another single down to third-man
length ball on off stump, the batsman drives it on the up down to long-off
a slower ball wide outside off, Powell waits in the crease and cuts it late down to third-man for another single
he is continuously bowling those slower ones now, this one bounces from a length and hits the batsman on his thigh pad. They call for a quick single as it drops close by
short of length delivery on off stump, defended back down the pitch
Powell brings up a fifty with a soft push towards mid-off. Oh there are more runs as Wade misses a throw at this end and the batsmen take the overthrows
immediately charges out, but doesn't get hold of the low full-toss, hits it tamely towards deep midwicket
now Powell leaves the crease on a tossed up one drifting towards leg, he flicks it to deep square leg
tossed up outside off, he pushes it towards point off the front foot
pushed through on the middle stump line, who has to defend after he had moved out of the crease
he places the tossed up delivery on the leg side and they run two as the fielders are deep
flighted on off stump line, Bravo comes forward to defend the ball down on the pitch
another leg-spinning slower one and Powell has had enough of it, he drives it over the fielder at short cover and the timing does the rest..
similar delivery, but it's on off stump and is slightly shorter, gives enough time to Powell to rock back and smash it to deep midwicket boundary
gets beaten as he tries to steer a length ball outside off down to third man
zooper!! another leg cutter and another one hit over extra cover for a one-bounce four.. That slower one is not working in this over at all
time to put those slower balls in your closet, this one is sent over the bowler's head for the fourth boundary in this over
fuller length delivery outside off, he comes forward and eases it to deep cover to keep the strike
flatter delivery outside off, Powell dabs it point off the back foot
two steps down the pitch and he crunches it over the umpire's head for another boundary..
mid-on had no chance as Powell is skating at high speed. He came out and muscled it straight down the ground
flighted delivery on the middle stump line, defended back to the bowler
sweeps this one from around middle and leg to deep backward square leg for a single
Maxwell gets a wicket!! It was a flatter delivery from round the wicket and Bravo went for a cute little late cut and ended up edging it to the keeper. Leaves straight away, Maxwell roars..
he gets a low full-toss outside off, drives it straight down to long-off for a single
back of length delivery, Pollard drops it on the leg side and calls for a quick single, Powell had to dive to get in..
hits him on the pads as Powell comes forward to play the length ball on the off side, McKay lets out an appeal, but that would have gone over
short of length delivery on off stump, pushed to point off the back foot
length ball down the leg side, Powell goes for a pull, but the ball does not bounce high enough, hits him around thigh pad and rolls towards the leg side
length ball on off stump, Pollard comes solidly behind the ball and defends it towards mid-on
gets a full length ball wide outside off and he waits and opens the face to run it down past first slip for a boundary
145k attempted yorker, it ends up being a low full-toss, but it's still too quick and goes under the bat to the keeper

another yorker, this time on the off and middle stump, Powell digs it out and Mitchell Starc catches it in return. Australians appeal for lbw as the ball might have hit the pad before the bat. the umpire says not out and they ask for a review. It hits the pads first..and it was going to hit off and middle. Starc takes out Powell.

gets a short ball on off stump which goes past the outside edge as the batsman tries to sway away.. Everyone goes up on an appeal for caught behind. the umpire shakes his head, but they call for a review.. A brute of a delivery.. Hot-spot being tested. Was there some glove on it? Not sure...hot-spot not very conclusive.. They are checking for sound cues... too long being taken here (we are into the zone where DRS starts becoming a bit of a pain).. He gives him out.. on the sound cue.. Well, I thought ..Speechless I am..
fuller length a touch outside off and it's driven comfortably through the off side for runs
short of length delivery outside off, left alone by the batsman

caught at long on! The batting is crumbling! Pollard sees the flight and launches it into the skies, but it's not quite Wankhede so the ball doesn't go for a six, it comes down close the boundary where Finch takes a good catch. The wheels are coming off, it's official
bowls a full flighted delivery on off stump, it's defended down the pitch
tossed up on off and middle, he comes forward and pushes it down to long-on
pitches on middle and turns down the leg side, it hits the pads as the batsman tries to turn it to the leg side
on the pads again, and Sammy gets hit on the pads as he tries to flick it, the ball rolls to short fine leg
on the middle and leg line, defended to the leg side
full and wide, it's a low full-toss, Sammy rises above the drama and crunches it through cover for a boundary
short of length, but on the leg side, It hits the inside edge, then the thigh pad and trickles fine down the leg side. The keeper runs after it and hauls it back
short of length delivery on the body, goes towards backward square leg area, in the air as it was awkwardly fended off
short delivery on the body, the batsman gets under it comfortably
length ball outside the off stump, left alone by the batsman
short of length delivery on the middle and leg line, tucked to midwicket off the back foot
loopy delivery outside off, driven straight to cover
pushed through on off stump, punched back to the bowler
flatter delivery, pushed to cover off the back foot
another flatter delivery, pushed to midwicket
stays on the back foot and punches it to cover
spins in after pitching around middle and leg, the batsman comes forward to defend and gets hit on the thigh pad
length ball going across the right-hander, goes past the outside edge as Sammy has a poke at that one
cuts back in after pitching on short of length, hits it in the bit which is covered with some plastic.. Sammy stands tall and says he is ok.
short of length outside off, Sammy stays in the crease and pulls it to deep square leg
stands tall on the back foot and punches the short of length delivery outside off to deep cover
on the off stump, Sammy gets right behind it and defends it back to the bowler
length ball just outside off, Sammy stays out of the line and lets it go through
punched back to the bowler off the back foot
goes back and turns the flat delivery to the leg side, towards midwicket
tossed up to the batsman, defended off the front foot

caught at long off! boom! He was not to the pitch of the delivery, but he went for the big shot nonetheless, and just scoops it over to the fielder at long-off. And just like that, Maxwell has three. What a day for him!
full and flighted, pushed to extra cover off the front foot
flatter delivery on the pads, it's turned to the vacant square-leg area and the batsmen take a single
back of length on the middle stump line, defended towards the off side off the back foot
back of length on off stump, defended back to the bowler off the back foot
a quick short ball as Holder starts moving down the leg side, but the ball goes further down the leg side and is called a wide
back of length on the middle stump, defended back to the bowler
soooper shot from Holder! there is some batting talent in this guy. He makes room by moving outside leg stump and carves a length delivery over extra cover for a one-bounce four
full and fast yorker on off stump, easily dug out back down the pitch
moves outside leg and Mitchell follows him with the short one, Holder goes for a pull but doesn't connect
straight to the sight screen as Narine makes room and slogs it over the bowler's head for his first six
and another one, this one into the crowd beyond long-off
no. 3, to the same area as the previous one. Flighted, he charges down and smacks it over long-off
flatter delivery, makes do difference. He comes out and picks the ball of a length and goes over a leaping long-off fielder..
fires it wide outside off, Narine has to get back in crease  as soon as realises he is not going to reach it.
but he moves out of the crease again, and Maxwell fires it wide of off again. Narine takes long to come back to the crease, by that time, Wade has done his job.
length ball on off stump, Holder comes forward to defend, inside edges the ball to his pads
another shot that highlights Holder's potential. He drives this full ball beautifully but hits the stumps at the non-striker's end
moves way outside leg, Johnson follows him with a short ball, Holder flat bats it to mid-on
short ball down the leg side, everyone appeals for something, but it was way down the leg side
makes room and swats a short of length delivery to midwicket with the toe-end of his bat
comes up with the slower bouncer, but it goes over the batsman's head. Mitchell Johnson not very happy with the call.
fuller delivery on the off and middle, driven on the up to mid-off
short ball on the body, Holder takes a hit on his stomach as he tries to glance that
comes out of the pitch and drives it straight to cover. There is hesitation between the batsmen though and that costs Holder his wicket as he is inches short of the crease at the non-striker's end..
